-- site-doc.header: Properties:

Below are details of all properties of heading components. Each heading
component has title and body as common properties.

-- site-doc.component-property: `title`

`title` Title property of each heading is a default property. Below are title
font size, line-height and font-weight of each heading.

ðŸ”¶ h0: its `role` is \$inherited.types.heading-hero
- desktop: `font-size: 52, line-height: 60, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 700`
- mobile: `font-size: 52, line-height: 60, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 700`
- border-bottom: 1px solid \$inherited.colors.border(as per color scheme you use)

ðŸ”¶ h1: its `role` is \$inherited.types.heading-large
- desktop: `font-size: 40, line-height: 48, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 700`
- mobile: `font-size: 40, line-height: 48, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 700`
- border-bottom: 1px solid \$inherited.colors.border(as per color scheme you use)

ðŸ”¶ h2: its `role` is \$inherited.types.heading-medium
- desktop: `font-size: 32, line-height: 44, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 600`
- mobile: `font-size: 32, line-height: 44, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 600`

ðŸ”¶ h3: its `role` is \$inherited.types.heading-small
- desktop: `font-size: 24, line-height: 36, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 500`
- mobile: `font-size: 24, line-height: 36, letter-spacing: 0, weight: 500`

ðŸ”¶ h4: its `role` is \$inherited.types.heading-tiny
